Address is the IP address and port of the SNMP trap receiver.
Format: "<host>:<port>" (e.g., "192.0.2.1:162").
Password is the authentication password for SNMPv3.
Protocol specifies the authentication protocol.

single_nested.description:
Authentication contains the protocol and password used to authenticate SNMPv3 messages.
Required if SecurityLevel is "auth-no-priv" or "auth-priv".

string.description:
Community is the SNMP community string for SNMPv2c.
Ignored for SNMPv3. Acts as a simple shared password in SNMPv2c.

EngineID is the unique identifier of the remote SNMP engine.
Used in SNMPv3 for secure communication and context identification.
Password is the encryption password for SNMPv3.
Protocol specifies the privacy (encryption) protocol.

single_nested.description:
Privacy contains the encryption protocol and password for securing SNMPv3 messages.
Required if SecurityLevel is "auth-priv".

string.description:
SecurityLevel defines the security level for SNMPv3 communication.
Required for SNMPv3 only.
Supported values:
- "no-auth-no-priv": no authentication, no privacy
- "auth-no-priv": authentication only
- "auth-priv": authentication and privacy (encryption)

bool.description: If true the destination supports Inform PDUs.

string.description:
User is the SNMPv3 username used for authentication and privacy.
Required for SNMPv3 when using "auth-no-priv" or "auth-priv" levels.

Version specifies the SNMP protocol version to use for trap messages.
Supported values: "v1", "v2c", "v3".
